# Quality gates (Makefile)

This project uses `Makefile` targets for linting and testing.

## After every code change

When you finish a batch of edits, run:

```bash
make lint
```

Fix any lint failures before considering the work done. Do not leave lint broken.

## Before every commit

When the user asks you to commit (or you are about to commit), run:

```bash
make test
```

Only proceed with the commit if tests pass. Fix failures first.

## Setup

If tooling is missing, run `make install` once to create `.venv` and install dev dependencies.
